Right off of the bastille square is this small peaceful gem. Coming here to read a book in the middle of the day can make a nice small getaway. The houseboats are lovely and so is the garden. There is a small area for kids to play as well. Not one of paris.s must see.s, but if you're in the area, definetley pass through...

This site is located just off the Bastille square and runs down to the River Seine destination if one goes the whole route.. there are easy strolling paths, bridges to access , restaurants available, plenty of places to rest, visually stunning environment, a place to go for lunchtime, many opportunities available...

Down the stairs, near the water canal, you find a nice parc, where people read a book or play the guitar. Relaxing atmosphere, to enjoy a walk and take some sun. Also there are boats and panoramic view.

Nice place to have a break with a small picnic. Surprisingly calm near such a busy metro station Bastille. There are places for kids, benches, grass. Also nice walking path around. Perfect to take a pause during intense working/touristic day in Paris. Well located.

It's a great place to see couples in the grass, forgetting that they're in public, seriously people get a room. Also amazing amount of good boys walking by non stop, i had to tell my dog to stop starting fights....

Very calm and peaceful, it's lovely to see the boats floating over the water. It is a nice place to relax and enjoy the view. And maybe drink some wine or some beer!

It was recently completely rebuilt. It is all green now. With a huge willow tree and flowery bushes. Boats are attached to the docks. There is a pedestrian bridge over the basin. One end goes to the Seine river. Th√© other goes to the Bastille column. Two years work for a superb result.

This oft overlooked garden just next to Bastille is very well maintained and well worth a stroll. Hopefully it will stay that way... the Paris city hall is unfortunately not famed for its ability to conserve such spaces.

A city harbour in a beautiful setting. Even though it is in the heart of Paris, there is something relaxing and soothing about this place because it feels like a peaceful escape from the big city. The water is clear as day after they cleaned it a couple of years ago, and if you're by boat. it's a great base to boat up the Canal towards the Bassin de la Vilette or head to the Seine southwards. The harbour facilities are decent and the people at the capitainerie are very friendly.
A pleasant place to relax a few steps from the Place de la Bastille. Long stretch of water and lawn to contemplate the moored barges.
Are great little garden nestled in Central Paris. You can't go wrong here. Bring a picnic basket in a blanket and a lover!
